a short script to setup vscode env 

to run this script, you need to have "cabal" installed.

execute in the root of the project.

```
cabal run SetupVscodeEnv
```

 
and then drag the executable(1) to your project folder.

(1) the executable is the file named "SetupVscodeEnv",
you can find it in cabal build directory, usually it is "./dist/build/SetupVscodeEnv/SetupVscodeEnv"